WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:31.820 --> 00:00:36.950
If you mistakenly chose to be nice to the
weird kid in school, then, after you ignored

00:00:36.950 --> 00:00:42.470
some of their messages, they committed ritualistic
suicide so they could possess and murder your

00:00:42.470 --> 00:00:45.210
friends and family so you could experience
their loneliness, what could you do?

00:00:45.210 --> 00:00:50.431
In this video on Nerd Explains, I'll tell
you how to beat the Computer Witch, in, Friend

00:00:50.431 --> 00:00:51.431
Request.

00:00:51.431 --> 00:00:54.800
Let’s say we are Laura in the beginning
of the movie.

00:00:54.800 --> 00:00:59.260
We don’t have perfect knowledge and we don’t
know how this ends, all we know is what the

00:00:59.260 --> 00:01:00.640
characters know.

00:01:00.640 --> 00:01:02.440
Can we beat this situation?

00:01:02.440 --> 00:01:04.050
Let’s find out.

00:01:04.050 --> 00:01:09.630
We start out as a popular, good-looking college
girl, with so many friends, so many, just

00:01:09.630 --> 00:01:11.729
look at the facebook friend counter.

00:01:11.729 --> 00:01:17.430
When grabbing lunch between classes, we glance
over and see a weird loner girl checking us

00:01:17.430 --> 00:01:19.720
out from across the cafeteria.

00:01:19.720 --> 00:01:23.040
Apparently she is in our psych class as well.

00:01:23.040 --> 00:01:28.030
Later that night, she sends us a friend request
saying she’s from our psych class and hopes

00:01:28.030 --> 00:01:29.470
we can be friends, with a smiley face.

00:01:29.470 --> 00:01:32.440
This is the first important decision we need
to make.

00:01:32.440 --> 00:01:36.740
I’d say denying her friend request is perfectly
justified.

00:01:36.740 --> 00:01:38.090
Let me explain why.

00:01:38.090 --> 00:01:43.250
We take a look at her profile and she has
zero friends, zero.

00:01:43.250 --> 00:01:48.060
Every picture is put through a black and white
filter, and all her posts and images are really

00:01:48.060 --> 00:01:49.369
dark and goth.

00:01:49.369 --> 00:01:54.420
It’s abundantly clear we have literally
nothing in common with this girl.

00:01:54.420 --> 00:01:59.000
The fact that she immediately wants to be
friends when she doesn’t even know us is

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:00.479
a bit concerning.

00:02:00.479 --> 00:02:05.550
We haven’t hung out, participated in a study
group, or said anything to each other.

00:02:05.550 --> 00:02:09.420
The only interaction we’ve had is seeing
her creepily check us out from across the

00:02:09.420 --> 00:02:10.729
cafeteria.

00:02:10.729 --> 00:02:14.700
There is nothing that should give us any reason
to become friends all the sudden.

00:02:14.700 --> 00:02:18.900
I mean, I know this is college and people
are more willing to branch out and make friends

00:02:18.900 --> 00:02:21.930
with strangers, but still, it’s strange.

00:02:21.930 --> 00:02:24.700
Her animations and artwork are really good.

00:02:24.700 --> 00:02:29.121
Considering the timeline, she’s completing
these and posting these like every day, which

00:02:29.121 --> 00:02:31.560
would require a ton of skill.

00:02:31.560 --> 00:02:33.360
This chick is talented.

00:02:33.360 --> 00:02:37.250
Which means it’s even weirder that she has
zero friends.

00:02:37.250 --> 00:02:41.889
How can someone with that talent and pronounced
set of beliefs not find a friend.

00:02:41.889 --> 00:02:46.449
I’m sure plenty of people would be interested
in either talking with her about her sulky

00:02:46.449 --> 00:02:49.610
shit, or hiring her for her artistic abilities.

00:02:49.610 --> 00:02:53.800
This isn’t Salem where there’s twenty
uptight dicks in a medieval village.

00:02:53.800 --> 00:02:55.970
It’s 2016 with the internet.

00:02:55.970 --> 00:03:01.360
You can be the strangest, most fringe lunatic
imaginable and still find friends.

00:03:01.360 --> 00:03:06.500
I don’t think it’s possible to not find
one decent, actual friend in the 4 billion

00:03:06.500 --> 00:03:10.609
active internet users or 8 billion people
on this planet.

00:03:10.609 --> 00:03:15.040
For christ’s sake there are entire groups
of people that dress up in animal suits and

00:03:15.040 --> 00:03:19.230
fuck each other, and you can’t find one
friend, really?

00:03:19.230 --> 00:03:24.570
She should have at least some friends, unless
ya know, there’s something horribly wrong

00:03:24.570 --> 00:03:25.840
with her.

00:03:25.840 --> 00:03:30.940
Maybe she wants a real life friend that models
what she considers to be the perfect life,

00:03:30.940 --> 00:03:33.820
as an escape from her own deficiencies.

00:03:33.820 --> 00:03:38.220
Maybe like Laura said, she’s just new and
started her Facebook profile.

00:03:38.220 --> 00:03:41.120
Okay, but that’s super easy to check.

00:03:41.120 --> 00:03:45.540
Facebook literally tells you when she created
her profile, not to mention you can scroll

00:03:45.540 --> 00:03:50.010
her newsfeed or images to quickly see the
first post they made.

00:03:50.010 --> 00:03:54.340
Considering she has zero friends, I’d check
to see if it was a new profile.

00:03:54.340 --> 00:03:55.340
If it wasn’t new, that’s even weirder.

00:03:55.340 --> 00:03:56.340
In the movie, Laura doesn’t click on her
images, which is the most laughable, unlikely

00:03:56.340 --> 00:03:57.340
mistake.

00:03:57.340 --> 00:03:58.340
A college girl who's obsessed with social
media doesn’t check out the images section

00:03:58.340 --> 00:03:59.340
of someone’s Facebook profile, right.

00:03:59.340 --> 00:04:00.340
If we did check this creepy girl's images
to see when her first post was, or just to

00:04:00.340 --> 00:04:01.340
